    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on</span><span class=\"english\"> “</span><span class=\"english\">Bullying and Its Types</span><span class=\"english\">” </span><span class=\"english\">within 10 sentences.</span><span> </span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Bullying and Its Types</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Bullying is the repeated misuse of power through verbal, social, or physical </span><span class=\"english\">behaviour</span><span class=\"english\"> that causes harm. It is a serious problem that can damage both the mind and body of the victim. Verbal bullying includes name-calling, teasing, taunting, inappropriate comments, and threats of harm. Social bullying happens when someone is intentionally excluded, denied friendship, or targeted by spreading </span><span class=\"english\">rumours</span><span class=\"english\">. This form is dangerous because it creates isolation and emotional pain. Physical bullying involves hitting, pushing, tripping, spitting, or breaking someone’s belongings. Such actions often cause injuries and leave lasting fear in the victim. All three types of bullying can lower self-esteem, reduce confidence, and lead to long-term mental health issues. Young people are especially at risk because they cannot always resist or seek help. To stop bullying, families, schools, and communities must work together and create safe, supportive environments for everyone.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Marks ----------------------------------------------09 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For </span><span class=\"english\">Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Bullying and Its Types</span><span class=\"english\">) -------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> -----------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Bullying is the repeated misuse of power through verbal, social, or physical </span><span class=\"english\">behaviour</span><span class=\"english\"> that causes harm. </span><span class=\"english\">(C) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Bullying Overview</span><span class=\"english\">) (Any 6 Points) </span><span class=\"english\">----</span><span class=\"english\">06 Marks  </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Involves name-calling, teasing, taunting, inappropriate comments, and threats.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Intentional exclusion, denied friendship, or spreading rumors.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Physical actions causing injuries and lasting fear.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• All three types can lower self-esteem, reduce confidence, and lead to long-term mental health issues.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Young people are particularly at risk due to inability to resist or seek help.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Collaboration between families, schools, and communities to create safe, supportive environments.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion </span><span class=\"english\">-----------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">To stop bullying, families, schools, and communities must work together and create safe, supportive environments for everyone.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. (Comment: Write within single/one para). </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4. For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark. (comment: Write the Title /</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Bullying and Its Types)</span></p><p></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Explain the proverb:</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">“Look before you leap”</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">The proverb</span><span class=\"english\"> \"Look before you leap\"</span><span class=\"english\"> means that we should think carefully before taking any action, especially important or risky ones. Just like a person should check the ground before jumping, we should consider the possible results of our decisions before doing something. If we act without thinking, we may face problems or make mistakes. This saying teaches us to be wise, cautious, and plan ahead. Whether it’s starting a new job, making a big purchase, or taking any big step in life, it is always better to understand the risks and be prepared before moving forward.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Mark Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">A) Theme of The Proverb-----------------01 mark</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">• The proverb illustrates </span><span class=\"english\">that </span><span class=\"english\">we should think carefully before taking any action, especially important or risky ones.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">B) Context of The Proverb (</span><span class=\"english\">Look before you leap</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">( 03</span><span class=\"english\"> points) -----03 marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Encourages careful consideration before taking risky actions.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Similar to checking the ground before jumping, considering potential outcomes is crucial.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Emphasizes the need for wisdom, caution, and planning.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">C) Conclusion ----------- 01 Mark</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">Ultimately, this proverb highlights the </span><span class=\"english\">importance of understanding risks and being prepared before </span><span class=\"english\">moving forward.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">[N.B. For every 03 spelling or grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.]</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Make meaningful sentences with the following words.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Disseminate, Perceived, Extravagant, Scorned, </span><span class=\"english\">Immediately</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Disseminate (Verb) = Leaders </span><span class=\"english\">disseminate</span><span class=\"english\"> information through books, speeches and media to influence society and inspire collective progress. </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Perceived (</span><span class=\"english\">Verb)  =</span><span class=\"english\"> The joke was </span><span class=\"english\">perceived</span><span class=\"english\"> as mean by the others in the group.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Extravagant (Adjective) = The </span><span class=\"english\">extravagant</span><span class=\"english\"> wedding ceremony was filled with luxurious decorations and food.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Scorned (Verb) = She </span><span class=\"english\">scorned</span><span class=\"english\"> their views as old-fashioned.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Immediately (Adverb) = Please report the issue </span><span class=\"english\">immediately</span><span class=\"english\"> so we can fix it.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Immediately (Conjunction) = </span><span class=\"english\">Immediately</span><span class=\"english\"> she’d gone, I remembered her name.</span><span class=\"english\"> [Students can use it both as Adverb and Conjunction]</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><a></a><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">i</span><span class=\"english\">)</span><span class=\"english\"> Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\"> (iii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For </span><span class=\"english\">02</span><span class=\"english\"> spelling mistakes, </span><span class=\"english\">01 mark</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted, for </span><span class=\"english\">01 spelling</span><span class=\"english\"> mistake, </span><span class=\"english\">0.5 marks</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted from that very sentence.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\"> (iv)</span><span class=\"english\"> For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a </span><span class=\"english\">suffix or prefix</span><span class=\"english\">, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the </span><span class=\"english\">subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number</span><span class=\"english\">, etc.)</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎Comment: </span><span class=\"english\">Use the given word without changing its parts of speech</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p>"
